  <prompt>
    Add a `SideEffect` case to `PlaybookOutputHandler.HandleOutputAsync` that emits NO user-visible chat or workspace content but DOES emit structured telemetry (tier-1 safe per ADR-015) recording the side-effect dispatch event with `{playbookId, playbookName, tenantId}`. Implements spec FR-14d SideEffect branch.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer. Expert in `PlaybookOutputHandler` + ADR-015 audit telemetry (tier-1 safe: no user-content fields).</role>

  <goal>
    `PlaybookOutputHandler.HandleOutputAsync` SideEffect case logs a structured telemetry event (no PII, no user-message content, no file content). No SSE event emitted; no chat token emitted. Unit test verifies telemetry captured + no user-visible output. ADR-015 audit memory tier compliance preserved.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec FR-14d SideEffect branch + design §1.3. SideEffect destinations are for playbooks that do background work (e.g., logging, telemetry, batch processing) without user-visible output. The telemetry-only branch makes these dispatches observable for ops without surfacing them to the user.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/PlaybookOutputHandler.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Telemetry/</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Handler in `Services/Ai/Chat/`; AI-internal.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Telemetry tier-1 safe: no user message content, no file content, no recall results. Fields limited to deterministic IDs + names.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Per-task BFF publish-size measurement.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-14d SideEffect: emit NO user-visible content.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Wave 3-B parallel safe — distinct switch arm.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/design.md</file>
